'''aluminosilicate'''
#{{chemistry}} any of many [[silicate]] [[mineral]]s, such as [[feldspar]] and [[zeolite]], in which a [[proportion]] of the Si<sup>4+</sup> [[ion]]s are replaced by Al<sup>3+</sup>, the excess [[negative]] [[charge]] being balanced by extra [[sodium]], [[potassium]] or [[calcium]] ions

